AUDIO: 'So Cloudflare are working on something called Artifact, a distributed file system that\'s Git compatible and is built for agents first and lets you programmatically create, fork, or delete thousands of repos, no matter how small or big they are, for things like'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'parallel PR reviews, automated refactoring of large codebases, and per-session agent workspaces. But, with this being built on top of Durable Objects, does that mean you have to use JavaScript and you can\'t have access to a shell command to run Git? Hit'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'subscribe and let\'s find out. GitHub was built for humans, not for agents, meaning they don\'t need any of these social aspects, so followers, stars, discussions, but agents are very'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'good at Git. It\'s in their training data. So Cloudflare have built a basic Git implementation in Zig, compile it to WASM, and put it on a Durable Object to act as a Git server. Meanwhile, the'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'client itself can be anything you want. So a worker using isomorphic Git inside a worker or using the Git protocol and even the HTTP client so that you can connect to it for things that don\'t use'

